tik,picked,narrative
"1","Although more widely recorded than other species of the genus (records from Sussex to Kent and north to Lancashire and Yorkshire plus Scotland - Dumfries & Galloway, Lanarkshire, Highlands) most records pre-date the assessment period. Biology has been well studied with host in GB from Typhloybinae, Cicadellidae (leaf hoppers). Recorded hosts for England are Alebra albastriella (Fallén), Kybos smaragdulus (Fallén), Alnetoidia alneti (Dahlbom), Eupterycyba jacunda (Herrich-Schäffer), Fagocyba cruenta (Herrich-Schäffer), Lindllergina aurovittata (Douglas), Ribautiana tenerrima (Herrich-Schäffer), Typhlocyba quercus (Fabricius).","Insufficient data were available to reach a supportable conclusion on the threat status for this taxon."
"2","A less well recorded member of the genus, this parasitoid / predator of Typhlobinae, Cicadellidae (leaf hoppers) has been recorded from Surrey, Cambridgeshire, Norfolk and South Yorkshire.","Insufficient data were available to reach a supportable conclusion on the threat status for this taxon."
"3","This dryinid wasp acts as a parasitoid/predator on Typhloybinae, Cicadellidae (Leafhopper). A recorded host in Britain is Eurhadina concinna (Germar). Sparsely recorded from Hampshire to Kent and north to Lancashire and Co, Durham in England and also known from Scotland (Dumfries & Galloway, Highlands).","Insufficient data were available to reach a supportable conclusion on the threat status for this taxon."
"4","This species has been recorded from Devon to Kent and north to Cheshire and Co. Durham in England, Wales (Denbighshire, Swansea) and is widespread in Scotland from Dumfries & Galloway to Highlands. A parasitoid/predator on Leaf Hoppers Typhloybinae (Cicadellidae (Leafhoppers) and hosts from GB include Alnetoidea almeti (Dahlbom), Dryocyha carri (Edwards), Edwardsiana avellanae (Edwards), E. flavescens (Fabricius), E. geometrica (Schanck), E. hippocastoni (Edwards), E. rosae (Linnaeus), Fagocyba crueata ((Herrich-Schäffer), Ossiannilssonola callosa (Thon),Riautiana ulmi (Linnaeus), Typhlocyba quercus (Fabricius) and Typhlocyba crataegi (Douglas).","Insufficient data were available to reach a supportable conclusion on the threat status for this taxon."
"5","Also known as A. heidelbergensis, Richards, 1939, the species - a parasitoid / predator on Typhlobinae, Cicadellidae (leaf hoppers) - has been recorded from Hampshire, Surrey, Cambridgeshire, Herefordshire and Worcestershire though it's true distribution is unknown.","Insufficient data were available to reach a supportable conclusion on the threat status for this taxon."
"6","Also known as A. holommelas Richards, 1939 in Perkins (1976). Records of this dryinid wasp are from Devon to Kent and north to Cheshire and Co. Durham, Wales (Glamorgan, Pembrokeshire) and Scotland (Dumfries and Galloway, Lanarkshire, Edinburgh, Lothian, Angus, Highlands) which is almost certainly a true reflection of it's distribution. It acts as a parasitoid/predator on Typhloybinae,Cicadellidae (Leaf Hoppers) and has been reared from Lebra albastriella (Fallén), A. wahlbergi (Boheman), Eupteryx aurata Linnaeus), E. cyclops Matsumura, E. melissae (Curtis), E. urticae (Fabricius), E.hippocast (Edwards), Fagocyha cruenta (Herrich-Schäffer), Ribautiana tenerrima (Herrich-Schäffer), R. ulmi )Linnaeus) and also recorded on Typhlocyba opaca on apple.","Insufficient data were available to reach a supportable conclusion on the threat status for this taxon."
"7","","Insufficient data were available to reach a supportable conclusion on the threat status for this taxon."
