"103","Modern interpretation (Skinner & Jarmin, in press) suggests that Myrmica lonae: iso. Seifert: 2000 and Myrmica sabuleti: iso. Elmes: 1978 are one species. Accordingly, Myrmica sabuleti agg: iso. Elmes: 1978 has been assessed as one species for this Red List and Myrmica lonae: iso. Seifert: 2000 is not evaluated.",
"104","Added to the British list ini 2003 (Elmes), it is known that the species favours warm, boggy areas (where it nests in grass tussocks), though beyond this details on biology and ecology are lacking. ","Insufficient data were available to reach a supportable conclusion on the threat status for this taxon."
