"144","A peri-assessment colonist, this solitary bee was first found in 2008 on a site in East Surrey. Since 2006, it has been recorded 8 times in Surrey, West Sussex, Kent and Suffolk though these records may represent isolated colonisations from mainland Europe with little evidence of linking populations. ",
