"241","There are only 3 records – one from East Kent (pre-1850) and two more recent records. The recent records (2004 and 2008 – Leicestershire, C. O’Toole) could have been synanthropic colonists from imported bee hotels or misidentifications and the older record could have been a vagrant. With such a limited set of data – which is not robust – it has been decided that this species should not be evaluated.",
