"461","This bethyloid wasp is a predator on the larvae of Nocturnal Black Beetles (Tenebrionidae, Coleoptera), though nothing else is known of it's biology and ecology and there are only verified records for three locations in southern England (from Dorset to Surrey).","Insufficient data were available to reach a supportable conclusion on the threat status for this taxon."
