"196",""," The most threatening accepted population change estimate is -7.0% (tetrad area), which does not exceed the 30% decline required for qualification as VU under Criterion A. The EoO (232,200 km²) exceeds the 20,000 km² VU threshold for criterion B1 and does not satisfy sufficient subcriteria to reach a threat status, and the AoO (1,988 km²) is below the 2,000 km² VU threshold for criterion B2 but does not satisfy sufficient subcriteria to reach a threat status. For Criterion D2, the number of locations was greater than 5 and there is no plausible threat that could drive the taxon to CR or RE in a very short time. No information was available on population size to inform assessments against Criteria C and D1; nor were any life-history models available to inform an assessment against Criterion E."
"197",""," The most threatening accepted population change estimate is 55.0% (discrete Extent of Occurrence), which does not exceed the 30% decline required for qualification as VU under Criterion A. The EoO (111,700 km²) exceeds the 20,000 km² VU threshold for criterion B1 and does not satisfy sufficient subcriteria to reach a threat status, and the AoO (372 km²) is below the 500 km² EN threshold for criterion B2 but does not satisfy sufficient subcriteria to reach a threat status. For Criterion D2, the number of locations was greater than 5 and there is no plausible threat that could drive the taxon to CR or RE in a very short time. No information was available on population size to inform assessments against Criteria C and D1; nor were any life-history models available to inform an assessment against Criterion E."
"198","This species is only known from Scotland: Morayshire (Aviemore, Loch Garten), East Perth (Blair Atholl) and Wigtownshire (Whithorn). Although it is known to be a parasite of Osmia inermis, a record from 1986 in a habitat that does not fit either Osmia inermis or O. uncinata is a strong suggestion that the host specificity of this species is not fully understood, which complicates targeted survey effort.","Insufficient data were available to reach a supportable conclusion on the threat status for this taxon."
"267","Due to unresolved taxonomic and nomenclatural issues this species has not been evaluated.",
